Ask HN: Who is looking for a co-founder?
text:
The YC S23 applications have an April 7th Deadline.

The recent AI boom might do to the world what Mobile & Internet did when they came out. That coupled with the possibility of a recession makes it a nice time to start a business. The productivity gains unlocked by AI could find adoption quicker in this market than a bubbly market. Real estate is cheaper, people are cheaper to hire, advertisement spots might become cheaper and for the first time in years developers are looking for jobs & getting laid off at fairly big companies.

I am London based. I am a Software Engineer with about 5-7 years of experience working in both big tech and startups.

Ask HN: How to Build AI Crawler?
text: Hi, I'm working on a graph-based content aggregator, and I need a crawler to feed it. The idea behind using a graph is that the information is precisely sorted and categorized. The crawler should understand if the page is, for example, a general article, tutorial, curiosity, or tips&tricks and assign a link to the right node. It should also understand the context and distinguish an article on security where you mention javascript from a javascript course where you mention security and put them in different places. Do you think it is possible? I was looking for existing solutions but couldn't find any. Anyone wants to help me with building one? The aggregator is at https://library.one
